<P>Well, Pierrot, interrupted Alphon&s;o, I &s;hould not like to hurt any one, but methinks war mu&s;t be glorious &s;port&mdash;&s;o grand&mdash;trumpets &s;ounding&mdash;hor&s;es neighing&mdash;arms cla&s;hing&mdash;the king ap|plauding.&mdash;Oh God! Oh God it mu&s;t be de|lightful&punc;&mdash;Where did you collect all tho&s;e ideas, my dear, dear boy, &s;aid the Baron, appearing &s;uddenly, for &s;urely you &s;peak as feelingly, and as pertinently too, as if you had been already engaged. I have read of them, Sir, returned Al|pho&s;o, and I think I &s;hould like to try them.&mdash;And try them thou &s;halt, my love, &s;aid the Ba|ron, embracing him.</P>
