<P>And de&s;ire him, &s;aid the Baron, to open the li&s;ts, and permit me to call the villain to a public vindication of him&s;elf in &s;ingle combat, I think that you mi&s;take me yet, interrupted Don I&s;idor&mdash;Single combat indeed!&mdash;No, far be it from me to think of &s;taining, the noble warrior's &s;word with the blood of a murderer!&mdash;No, let ju&s;tice&mdash;</P>
<P>Hear me, Don I&s;idor, interrupted the Baron&mdash;hear my fixed re&s;olves&mdash;He mu&s;t fall by this arm&mdash;I cannot become an a&s;&s;a&s;&s;in or an execu|tioner&mdash;therefore I mu&s;t fight him&mdash;fear not thou the event&mdash;in &s;uch a cau&s;e, a pigmy's arm would wre&s;t victory from a giant: be&s;ides&mdash;but thou thinke&s;t that I am old&mdash;too old to&mdash;It may be &s;o&mdash;but know, I&s;idor, that even at this age, that man bears not arms in Spain from who&s;e cre&s;t Rayo would not now, even <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> old though he be, hope to pluck the laurel.</P>
