<P>Alas, my lord! returned the lady, is a lap&s;e of &s;o many, many years &s;pent in this dreary cell un|der all the mi&s;eries of anxiety and incertitude&mdash;is the re&s;olute endurance of violence, in&s;ult, and opprobrious abu&s;e&mdash;is the firmne&s;s with which I re&s;i&s;ted the active endeavours of your hireling prie&s;t, who betrayed his God, and u&s;ed the &s;acred privilege of confe&s;&s;or to pour pernicious poi&s;on in my ear, and act the pandar's part&mdash;is the for|titude with which I re&s;igned my infant to that death with which you menaced him, rather than wrong my mo&s;t beloved lord&mdash;are my vows &s;o|lemnly made and regi&s;tered in Heaven&mdash;are the mortifying &s;corn with which I have always treated your prote&s;tations, and my contempt and hatred of your hideous per&s;on&mdash;are tho&s;e fervent peti|tions which now for many, many years I have every hour of the undi&s;tingui&s;hed day and night wafted to Heaven with the &s;ighs of an afflicted heart, to &s;mite your guilty head and level it with the du&s;t&mdash;are all tho&s;e, I &s;ay, openly expre&s;&s;ed and every day avowed, yet in&s;ufficient to cor|rect the pre&s;umption of your heart, or convince you of the folly as well as wickedne&s;s of your hopes?&mdash;Unhappy wretch! Pity for who&s;e weak|ne&s;s would countervail my indignation for any crimes le&s;s than yours&mdash;begone!&mdash;or if nothing&punc; will convince your &s;en&s;ele&s;s vanity, nor <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> the fiend that works within you, but <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 span"> with blood, take my life&mdash;But oh! that would
