What name? exclaimed the lady exultingly&mdash;Oh, mother of mercy! perhaps it may&mdash;Oh if there were a name, the very &s;ound of which would bla&s;t open the gates of your concealment&mdash;dart vengeance quick as the piercing lightning through your ca&s;tle&mdash;and hurl you from your blind &s;ecurity!&mdash;Even now, &s;pite of your&s;elf, you betray your ba&s;e fears&mdash;and (rare union of cowardice and ra&s;hne&s;s!) while you tremble at the lion's roar, indulge in cruel &s;port, and goad its young one in the cage.</P>
